PURPOSE
  Shell script to output the top 20 most requested DNS lookups
  from a BIND DNS server.

STATUS
  Working as of: 2014-10-10

DETAILS
  This script will count and display the top 20 most requested
  DNS lookups from a BIND DNS server. Requires grep. Tested on
  Debian.

INSTALL
  01 : Include named.conf.topq in your named.conf file.
  02 : Create the /var/log/bind folder and ensure your BIND
       process has write permissions to it.
  03 : Copy to topq /usr/local/sbin and chmod +x.
  04 : Use and enjoy.

